			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't see how snare is the answer to our prayers.  It might help soloing a bit, but with our long casting spells it's not as effective as a wizard kiting.  Our rains aren't the same as the targetted AEs used to Quad-kite.
<br />

<br />
I think our solo-ability should be tied to our pets, just like it was back in the days of magely uberness.  To do that our pets need to be able to do something that keeps the mob off us while we nuke away.
<br />

<br />
Our pets should let us do things equivalent to the classes that have snare.  When us + our pets are tuned so we can solo at the Fire tables like druids, wizards, necros, even rangers - then I'll think we're close to where we should be for soloability.  I don't want to quad kite, I don't even necessarily want to kite.  As a class that thrived on soloing well into my 60's I think it only reasonable to expect that aspect of my class to remain constant.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">And who says if we get snare we cannot have uber pets to?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
