Not stellar is right.  Not too shabby?  I disagree.  Wizards are supposed to beat everyone at burst damage, rogues pull ahead on longer fights.  Since the rogues are beating out the wizards, it stands to reason that it was a longer fight.  In my opinion, mages should be right up in their faces when the number roll out (counting pets).  Since I seriously doubt those mages had pets that were putting out 30-35k damage, there's something lacking in our output.
<br />

<br />
I think our pets should be making up the difference, personally, and to that end let me say again, our pets should scale more appropriately as WE scale up with gear. With pets, assuming those mages were as skilled and well-equipped as the rogues and wizards, the total damage done per mage should be very close to the 75-80k mark - not slightly over HALF of the top damage dealer.
<br />

